<body class="bg-white">
    <%- include("../partials/header") %>

        <main class="py-8 bg-white">
            <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                    <article class="lg:col-span-2">
                        <div class="bg-white">
                            <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">
                                <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home</a>
                                <span class="mx-2">></span>
                                <a href="/cleaning" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Cleaning</a>
                                <span class="mx-2">></span>
                                <span class="text-gray-800">Organize Entryway</span>
                            </nav>

                            <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 leading-tight">
                                How to Organize a Busy Entryway Once and For All
                            </h1>

                            <div class="mb-8">
                                <img src="/images/organize-entryway.webp" alt="Neatly organized home entryway"
                                    class="w-full h-80 object-cover rounded-lg shadow-lg" fetchpriority="high">
                            </div>

                            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Introduction</h2>
                                <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                                    The entryway is the first thing you see when you come home and the last thing you
                                    see before you leave. Keeping it organized sets the tone for your entire day and
                                    helps prevent clutter from spreading into the rest of your house.
                                </p>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">The Landing Strip Method</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Create a specific spot for everything that enters your
                                    home. This prevents the "drop and go" habit that leads to entryway chaos.</p>
                                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
                                    <li><strong>Key Hooks:</strong> Never lose your keys again by having a dedicated
                                        place for them.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Mail Station:</strong> Sort mail immediately and have a tray for items
                                        that need action.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Trash Can:</strong> Keep a small bin nearby for junk mail and receipts.
                                    </li>
                                </ul>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Mastering Shoe and Bag Storage
                                </h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Shoes and bags are the biggest offenders in entryway
                                    clutter. Vertical and hidden storage are key.</p>
                                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
                                    <li><strong>Shoe Cabinets:</strong> Use slim, wall-mounted cabinets for a clean
                                        look.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Sturdy Hooks:</strong> Install hooks at different heights for adults and
                                        children.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Bench with Storage:</strong> A bench provides a place to sit and hidden
                                        storage for larger items.</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Conclusion</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700">
                                    A well-organized entryway isn't just about aesthetics—it's about making your daily
                                    routine smoother. Start by decluttering and then implement systems that work for
                                    your family's habits.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </article>

                    <aside class="lg:col-span-1">
                        <div class="sticky top-8 space-y-6">
                            <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
                                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Essential Items</h3>
                                <ul class="text-gray-600 space-y-2">
                                    <li>• Door mat</li>
                                    <li>• Key bowl/hooks</li>
                                    <li>• Shoe rack</li>
                                    <li>• Umbrella stand</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </aside>
                </div>
            </div>
        </main>

        <%- include("../partials/footer") %>
            <script src="/js/script.js"></script>
</body>

</html>